This paper deals with the problem of capacity region characterization in a multi-hop line network, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The focus on coordination and functional regimes suggests a systems and control perspective (cs.SY), while the use of randomness and message passing is relevant to distributed computing (cs.DC). Finally, the analysis of capacity regions involves optimization and game theory, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG).
